{"title":"Spotted: Ekoi Developing All-New Road Pedal Design with Huge Platform!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/spotted-ekoi-road-pedal-new-bolt-standard/","date":1706713579000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1440\" height=\"823\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal.jpg 1440w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal-800x457.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-pedal-768x439.jpg 768w\" /></p>\n<p>The French accessory powerhouse Ekoi is developing a new aero-top-of-the-line road pedal. If you follow the French continental team <a href=\"https://www.nicemetropolecotedazur.com/\">Nice Métropole </a>(you should), you’ll notice some pretty large clipless pedals on their rides.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"849\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180-800x849.jpeg\" alt=\"Ekoi PW8 road pedals best view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180-800x849.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180-283x300.jpeg 283w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180-113x120.jpeg 113w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180-768x815.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-best-view--scaled-e1706653860180.jpeg 1181w\" /><figcaption>(All photos / <a href=\"https://www.nicemetropolecotedazur.com/\">Nice Métropole</a><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/teamnicemetropolecotedazur/\" target=\"_blank\">/Instagram</a>)</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ekoi PW8 — What is it? </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The piece catching everyone off guard is the size of the platform of this new design. If you look at some of the photos posted on their Instagram account, it’s obvious. The pedal length compared to the crank arm is telling; this is a long, lean pedal.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The French cycling outlet <a href=\"https://lecycle.fr/actualites/ekoi-la-nouvelle-pedale-chaussure-pw8-pour-gagner-8-watts/49839/\">LeCycle.fr</a> first broke the news, reporting that the new Ekoi PW8 pedal will offer a modern twist to the road clipless pedal. The pedal may cover more surface area while also offering a thinner stack height. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"735\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-735x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Ekoi PW8 road pedals team top IG\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-735x1200.jpeg 735w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-184x300.jpeg 184w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-74x120.jpeg 74w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-768x1254.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702-941x1536.jpeg 941w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-team-top-IG--scaled-e1706654027702.jpeg 1173w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"555\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--555x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Ekoi PW8 road pedals close up bottom\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--555x1200.jpeg 555w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--139x300.jpeg 139w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--55x120.jpeg 55w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--768x1662.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--710x1536.jpeg 710w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--947x2048.jpeg 947w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-close-up-bottom--scaled.jpeg 1183w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From the picture above, it looks as if the ‘cleat’ may extend all the way to the edge of the shoe around the toe, with the pedal then recessed inside it when clipped in. That could result in a more aerodynamic connection between the pedal and shoe. It also could create a more walkable platform on the bottom of your shoes. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"555\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--555x1200.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--555x1200.jpeg 555w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--139x300.jpeg 139w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--55x120.jpeg 55w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--768x1662.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--710x1536.jpeg 710w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--947x2048.jpeg 947w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals--scaled.jpeg 1183w\" /><figcaption>(All Image credits: Instagram: Nice Métropole)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"793\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-793x1200.jpeg\" alt=\"Ekoi PW8 road pedals full team cafe\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-793x1200.jpeg 793w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-198x300.jpeg 198w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-79x120.jpeg 79w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-768x1162.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600-1015x1536.jpeg 1015w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Ekoi-PW8-road-pedals-full-team-cafe--scaled-e1706654054600.jpeg 1181w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>A New Standard? </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If that is the case, it seems likely this system could require a new mounting system, though it’s possible it could be added to a shoe around the traditional 3-bolt interface currently used by most pedals. We’re guessing that’s where the new Ekoi road shoes come into play.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>We contacted Ekoi for comment but all they would divulge at this time is that the pedal is currently being tested with various teams. If you want to learn more, I recommend watching the Nice Métropole Team, <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/burgosbh/?hl=en\">Burgos-BH Team</a>, or the Ekoi website.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/spotted-ekoi-road-pedal-new-bolt-standard/\">Spotted: Ekoi Developing All-New Road Pedal Design with Huge Platform!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a32f15d56c312512238502d7f07fb21d470ee4e6706320b070d6d8534a3971a4","category":"Cycling"}